article.headline: St. John's 73, E. Michigan 61
article.story: NEW YORK -- D.J. Kennedy scored 16 points to lead St. John's to a 73-61 win over Eastern Michigan on Monday night in the NIT Season Tip-Off. Justin Burrell had 14 points, Malik Booth had 11 and Paris Horne 10 for the Red Storm. Justin Dobbins and Brandon Bowdry each had 13 points for the Eagles (1-4), who have lost four in a row. St. John's (4-1) went on an 18-4 run after Dobbins' jumper opened the scoring.
